{"word":"H2218 - זֶרֶד - Zered - zeh'-red - Zared","slug":"H2218","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">זֶרֶד</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>Zered"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>zeh'-red"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Zared"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D6;&#x05E8;&#x05D3; - zered</b> - <i>zeh'-red</i><p/>From an unused root meaning to <i>be exuberant</i> in growth; lined with <i>shrubbery</i>; <i>Zered</i>, a brook East of the Dead Sea: - Zared, Zered."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H2215\">H2215</a>, <a href=\"#/H2216\">H2216</a>"}]}